headline: Sandisk Heads Into Earnings as AI Demand Lifts Outlook
summary: Last year, hard-drive maker  Western Digital  spun off its chip-based storage unit,  Sandisk  to unlock the value of this newer type of data storage, which has become increasingly important in data centers and consumer devices.  The strategy has paid off: Western Digital stock is up about 395%, and Sandisk shares have gained roughly 1,237% since their February listing through Tuesday’s closing prices.  When Sandisk reports its second-quarter earnings on Thursday afternoon, Wall Street analysts are looking for early signs of accelerating growth in sales and earnings.

headline: Western Digital (NASDAQ:WDC) Q4 Sales Beat Estimates, Inventory Levels Improve
summary: Leading data storage manufacturer Western Digital (NASDAQ: WDC) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 25.2% year on year to $3.02 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($3.2 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 6.8% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.13 per share was 10.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
